Description of the indicator \n(with def:
This is a new indicator which would complement data on social protection coverage to track the level of or extent to which Parties have adapted their social protection systems to better respond to climate change impacts. The indicator takes a scored approach, based on an assessment of a selected number of observable qualitative attributes. These will be defined during methodology development but should include: 
(1) extent of integration of climate risks in social protection policies, strategies and laws; 
(2) extent of integration of climate risks in social protection financing (incl links to disaster risk financing); 
(3) flexibility of social protection programmes, scalability protocols and linkages with EWS; 
(4) registry coverage and currency; 
(5) resilience of administrative systems; 
(6) linkages between social protection schemes and other livelihoods and employment programmes.

